<li><a href="http://www.gamji.com/article5000/NEWS5521.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.gamji.com/article5000/NEWS5521.htm" rel="nofollow">The Niger Delta Question: Incubating the Future Suicide Bombers of Nigeria</a>, by Hosiah Emmanuel</li>
<li><a href="http://globalguerrillas.typepad.com/globalguerrillas/2006/01/nigerian_evolut.html" class="external text" title="http://globalguerrillas.typepad.com/globalguerrillas/2006/01/nigerian_evolut.html" rel="nofollow">"NIGERIAN EVOLUTION"</a>, (Global Guerrillas) <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2006-01-16"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="01-16"><a href="/wiki/January_16" title="January 16">January 16</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/2006" title="2006">2006</a></span></li>
<li><a href="http://www.vanityfair.com/politics/features/2007/02/junger200702" class="external text" title="http://www.vanityfair.com/politics/features/2007/02/junger200702" rel="nofollow">Blood Oil</a> by <a href="/wiki/Sebastian_Junger" title="Sebastian Junger">Sebastian Junger</a> in <i><a href="/wiki/Vanity_Fair_(magazine)" title="Vanity Fair (magazine)">Vanity Fair</a></i>, February 2007 (accessed <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2007-01-28"><a href="/wiki/January_28" title="January 28">28 January</a> <a href="/wiki/2007" title="2007">2007</a></span>)</li>
<li><a href="http://www7.nationalgeographic.com/ngm/0702/feature3/index.html" class="external text" title="http://www7.nationalgeographic.com/ngm/0702/feature3/index.html" rel="nofollow">Nigerian Oil -- "Curse of the Black Gold: Hope and Betrayal in the Niger Delta"</a> -- article from <a href="/wiki/National_Geographic_Magazine" title="National Geographic Magazine">National Geographic Magazine</a> (February 2007)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.africamasterweb.com/AdSense/NigerianMilitants06Chronology.html" class="external text" title="http://www.africamasterweb.com/AdSense/NigerianMilitants06Chronology.html" rel="nofollow">"Chronology of Nigerian militants' Attacks"</a>, Masterweb News Desk (February 21, 2007)</li>
<li><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/6644097.stm" class="external text" title="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/6644097.stm" rel="nofollow">The shadowy militants in Nigeria's Delta</a> -- from the BBC (May 2007)</li>
<li><a href="http://blog.wired.com/defense/2007/05/q_tell_me_a_lit.html" class="external text" title="http://blog.wired.com/defense/2007/05/q_tell_me_a_lit.html" rel="nofollow">Inside the Brave New War, Part 1</a>, Wired <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2007-05-16"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="05-16"><a href="/wiki/May_16" title="May 16">May 16</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/2007" title="2007">2007</a></span>, interview with former Air Force counter-terrorism officer, technology analyst, and software entrepreneur about his book by the same name.</li>
<li><a href="http://stinet.dtic.mil/cgi-bin/GetTRDoc?AD=ADA471380&amp;Location=U2&amp;doc=GetTRDoc.pdf" class="external text" title="http://stinet.dtic.mil/cgi-bin/GetTRDoc?AD=ADA471380&amp;Location=U2&amp;doc=GetTRDoc.pdf" rel="nofollow">Emerging Requirements for US Counterinsurgency, An Examination of the Insurgency in the Niger River Delta</a></li>
</ul>
